goals.question: What is the correlation between u and v?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of u vs v
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is any relationship between the two variables. If there is a strong correlation, it can be used to predict one variable based on the other.

goals.question: What is the average value of u?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the median, quartiles, and outliers of the variable u. It can help to understand the central tendency of the data.

goals.question: What is the average value of v?

code:
```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['u'], color='blue', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='v', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['v'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['v'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['v'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['v'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('v')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of v?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x=data['u'], color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average value of u?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("u")
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x=data['v'], ax=ax, color='skyblue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['v'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    plt.title('What is the average value of v?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('v')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
